                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370508-name-902" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-902" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-902" type="surname" value="HEATH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370508-name-902" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY HEATH</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a labourer, and lodge in a room in Carlile-street, Lisson Grove. The prisoner slept in the same bed about three weeks—I missed a half crown, and one shilling, and some other things—on the 26th of April, I marked a shilling, and went to bed—in the morn<lb></lb>ing, when I got up at half-past four o'clock, the prisoner was there—I looked into my breeches pocket, and missed the shilling—I went out at half-past four o'clock, and returned with the policeman, who found one shilling in his pocket, and the duplicate of the six shifts which I had lost a fortnight after he came to me—these are the shifts.</p>
